is not a crime.

987
01:01:13.227 --> 01:01:14.560
illegally filling
a warehouse

988
01:01:14.561 --> 01:01:17.561
with too many people is.
Wait here. I gotta go find Oliver.

989
01:01:18.966 --> 01:01:20.866
Hey. hey. you two.
I need to see your ID.

990
01:01:20.867 --> 01:01:22.034
I was just leaving.

991
01:01:22.035 --> 01:01:25.035
Look. you can show me your ID.
or you can go to jail.

992
01:01:26.440 --> 01:01:29.440
Young lady. what was that you
just disposed of?

993
01:01:30.978 --> 01:01:33.978
Seventeen. huh? Don't you think
you're kind of far from home?

994
01:01:35.282 --> 01:01:36.649
That's why
I was leaving.

995
01:01:36.650 --> 01:01:38.784
Yeah. good idea.

996
01:01:38.785 --> 01:01:41.785
Hey. Hi. Come on.

997
01:01:42.756 --> 01:01:45.756
What do you say? Cherry Slurpees
to celebrate our last night?

998
01:01:54.301 --> 01:01:57.301
I gotta find Pash.

999
01:03:23.724 --> 01:03:26.724
I was
slicing up an avocado

1000
01:03:28.261 --> 01:03:31.261
When you came up behind me

1001
01:03:32.766 --> 01:03:35.766
With your silent
brand new sneakers

1002
01:03:37.337 --> 01:03:40.337
Your reflection
I did not see

1003
01:03:41.575 --> 01:03:44.575
It was the hottest day
in August

1004
01:03:46.380 --> 01:03:49.380
We were heading
for the sea

1005
01:03:50.917 --> 01:03:53.917
For a second
my mind started drifting

1006
01:03:55.522 --> 01:03:58.522
You put your arms
around me

1007
01:04:04.297 --> 01:04:07.297
You put your arms
around me

1008
01:04:13.407 --> 01:04:16.407
You put your arms around

1009
01:04:18.145 --> 01:04:21.145
From your mouth
speaks your lovely voice

1010
01:04:22.482 --> 01:04:25.482
The softest words
ever spoken

1011
01:04:27.320 --> 01:04:30.320
What's broken
can always be fixed

1012
01:04:31.892 --> 01:04:34.892
What's fixed will
always be broken

1013
01:05:01.655 --> 01:05:04.655
A heart that's

1014
01:05:05.192 --> 01:05:08.192
full up like a landfill

1015
01:05:11.331 --> 01:05:14.331
A job that
slowly kills you

1016
01:05:17.971 --> 01:05:20.971
Bruises that won't heal

1017
01:05:27.547 --> 01:05:30.547
You look so tired-unhappy

1018
01:05:33.854 --> 01:05:36.854
Bring down the government

1019
01:05:40.327 --> 01:05:43.327
They don't
They don't speak for us

1020
01:05:54.975 --> 01:05:57.975
Where the hell
have you been?

1021
01:05:58.578 --> 01:06:01.578
We got a phone call from Pash's
parents at about 3:00 in the morning.

1022
01:06:04.084 --> 01:06:06.418
That wasn't fun.

1023
01:06:06.419 --> 01:06:09.419
This is your SAT class?

1024
01:06:12.425 --> 01:06:15.425
Excuse me.
what are you doing?

1025
01:06:15.729 --> 01:06:17.496
You can't do that.
I paid for those.

1026
01:06:17.497 --> 01:06:20.497
Hey. you lied. kiddo. all right?
That dog ain't gonna hunt.

1027
01:06:21.935 --> 01:06:24.935
Okay. All right.
I screwed up.

1028
01:06:25.772 --> 01:06:27.840
I get it. but what
was I supposed to...

1029
01:06:27.841 --> 01:06:29.108
Was I supposed to
ask for permission?

1030
01:06:29.109 --> 01:06:30.442
I mean. you would
have just said no.

1031
01:06:30.443 --> 01:06:32.678
You're damn straight.
we would have said no.

1032
01:06:32.679 --> 01:06:34.113
What do you think

1033
01:06:34.114 --> 01:06:36.582
that the world thinks of those
girls with all their tattoos?

1034
01:06:36.583 --> 01:06:39.451
Do you think they have an
easy time finding a job?

1035
01:06:39.452 --> 01:06:42.452
Or getting
a loan application?

1036
01:06:42.455 --> 01:06:43.789
Or going to
a decent college?

1037
01:06:43.790 --> 01:06:45.190
I think it depends
on the girl.

1038
01:06:45.191 --> 01:06:46.959
Or finding a husband?

1039
01:06:46.960 --> 01:06:48.394
No. you just limit
your choices.

1040
01:06:48.395 --> 01:06:49.962
Seriously.
you need to stop.

1041
01:06:49.963 --> 01:06:51.797
You really need
to stop shoving

1042
01:06:51.798 --> 01:06:54.798
your psychotic idea of '50s
womanhood down my throat.

1043
01:06:58.772 --> 01:07:01.772
And pageants? I mean. what have
they ever done for you?

1044
01:07:02.542 --> 01:07:05.377
That's my point. Bliss.

1045
01:07:05.378 --> 01:07:06.745
I didn't have a mother

1046
01:07:06.746 --> 01:07:09.746
to navigate all my opportunities.
Jesus Christ.

1047
01:07:10.250 --> 01:07:13.250
I am in love with this.

1048
01:07:14.955 --> 01:07:17.122
I mean.
don't you get it?

1049
01:07:17.123 --> 01:07:19.158
It won't last.

1050
01:07:19.159 --> 01:07:22.159
in two or three years. it'll be over.
This is a moment.

1051
01:07:22.796 --> 01:07:25.796
Well. how great is that?

1052
01:07:26.433 --> 01:07:28.300
You don't understand.

1053
01:07:28.301 --> 01:07:30.636
You will when you have to
support yourself.

1054
01:07:30.637 --> 01:07:31.971
I do support myself.

1055
01:07:31.972 --> 01:07:33.572
No. you don't.

1056
01:07:33.573 --> 01:07:36.573
You buy shoes.

1057
01:07:43.183 --> 01:07:46.183
You're full of shit.

1058
01:07:46.419 --> 01:07:47.853
You know what.
actually...

1059
01:07:47.854 --> 01:07:49.021
Hey.

1060
01:07:49.022 --> 01:07:50.856
Hey. you calm down.
little lady.

1061
01:07:50.857 --> 01:07:53.359
Why don't you go back
to your turtle shell

1062
01:07:53.360 --> 01:07:56.360
so you don't have to
freaking confront anything?

1063
01:08:09.542 --> 01:08:12.542
You all right?

1064
01:08:14.881 --> 01:08:16.782
I just don't
wanna talk about it.

1065
01:08:16.783 --> 01:08:19.718
Pash. come on.

1066
01:08:19.719 --> 01:08:21.954
You told me
to wait for you.

1067
01:08:21.955 --> 01:08:24.223
I was so busy waiting for you
that I didn't notice the cop

1068
01:08:24.224 --> 01:08:26.325
coming over to arrest me
for an open container.

1069
01:08:26.326 --> 01:08:27.893
Shit. are you okay?

1070
01:08:27.894 --> 01:08:30.396
No. actually. I'm not okay.
all right?

1071
01:08:30.397 --> 01:08:33.397
On top of everything. my parents
decided to put a GPS in my car

1072
01:08:34.734 --> 01:08:37.734
so they can track
my every goddamn move.

1073
01:08:40.407 --> 01:08:42.474
So what's your problem?

1074
01:08:42.475 --> 01:08:45.077
Hope the joyride with your
boyfriend was worth it.

1075
01:08:45.078 --> 01:08:48.078
Wait. wait.
How is this my fault. okay?

1076
01:08:48.214 --> 01:08:49.581
I didn't put that
drink in your hand.

1077
01:08:49.582 --> 01:08:52.518
You know what? I'm ecstatic that
you have this whole new life

1078
01:08:52.519 --> 01:08:54.420
and you have all new friends
and it's great.

1079
01:08:54.421 --> 01:08:57.421
But I'm trying to get out of this
armpit of a town just as much as you.

1080
01:08:58.591 --> 01:09:00.859
And last time I checked.

1081
01:09:00.860 --> 01:09:03.860
getting arrested is not the
kind of extracurricular

1082
01:09:03.930 --> 01:09:06.930
that Ivy League schools
are looking for.

1083
01:09:07.367 --> 01:09:10.367
Do you really think that this roller derby
career of yours is going anywhere?

1084
01:09:13.339 --> 01:09:14.440
That's not what
it's about.

1085
01:09:14.441 --> 01:09:16.208
Oh. yeah. right.

1086
01:09:16.209 --> 01:09:19.209
I'm sorry. Pash.

1087
01:09:26.753 --> 01:09:28.687
Thanks for
letting me stay.

1088
01:09:28.688 --> 01:09:29.888
Anytime.

1089
01:09:32.625 --> 01:09:35.625
That's Riley back there.
He's my little man.

1090
01:09:38.732 --> 01:09:41.033
So that's why you never
come out with us?

1091
01:09:41.034 --> 01:09:43.802
Yeah. he pretty much owns
my ass. Don't you. Rile?

1092
01:09:43.803 --> 01:09:45.871
Uh-huh.
Uh-huh.

1093
01:09:45.872 --> 01:09:48.872
Okay. first stop. sitter.
Then the Warehouse.

1094
01:09:59.986 --> 01:10:02.986
Ruthless. Ruthless.
Ruthless.

1095
01:10:05.158 --> 01:10:08.158
Maven. Maven. Maven?

1096
01:10:08.728 --> 01:10:11.728
Hey. guess how old I am.

1097
01:10:12.732 --> 01:10:13.999
Twenty-seven?

1098
01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:17.000
Oh. that's sweet.

1099
01:10:17.003 --> 01:10:20.003
I'm 36.

1100
01:10:21.241 --> 01:10:24.076
Guess when I
started skating.

1101
01:10:24.077 --> 01:10:26.612
I was 31.

1102
01:10:26.613 --> 01:10:29.613
'Cause it took me that long to find
one thing that I was really good at.

1103
01:10:36.156 --> 01:10:39.156
And you know what?
I worked my ass off to get it.

1104
01:10:42.796 --> 01:10:45.664
Yeah. me. too.

1105
01:10:45.665 --> 01:10:48.665
It's too bad
you're only 17.

1106
01:10:50.003 --> 01:10:53.003
What do you think the league is
gonna say when they find that out?

1107
01:10:53.706 --> 01:10:56.706
Or your teammates. when they
find out you've been lying?

1108
01:10:57.544 --> 01:10:59.978
That's gonna be rough.
Maven. please. Look...

1109
01:10:59.979 --> 01:11:01.513
No. you look.

1110
01:11:01.514 --> 01:11:04.514
One day it will be your time. Ruthless.
but it's not your time now.

1111
01:11:05.118 --> 01:11:08.118
And if I was you. I wouldn't even bother
lacing up those skates.

1112
01:11:30.076 --> 01:11:31.243
Fuck.

1113
01:11:33.713 --> 01:11:36.582
It's Oliver. I'm running with
the bulls right now.

1114
01:11:37.717 --> 01:11:40.717
Hey. Oliver.

1115
01:11:41.254 --> 01:11:44.254
I just need to talk to you.
I... I'm calling you from a payphone.

1116
01:11:48.361 --> 01:11:51.361
Look. I've left home.

1117
01:11:53.700 --> 01:11:56.700
I... You know. this...
I don't...

1118
01:11:57.770 --> 01:12:00.172
I don't wanna do this
on voicemail.

1119
01:12:00.173 --> 01:12:03.173
so maybe you can get me
on Maggie's phone.

1120
01:12:04.944 --> 01:12:07.944
512-697-4998.

1121
01:12:10.383 --> 01:12:13.383
And then we can just...
We can talk later. Okay. bye.

1122
01:12:18.358 --> 01:12:20.459
Oink Joint.
- Hey. B.

1123
01:12:20.460 --> 01:12:21.727
Hey. Bliss.

1124
01:12:21.728 --> 01:12:24.728
Is Pash there?

1125
01:12:25.198 --> 01:12:28.198
She's not here.

1126
01:12:30.970 --> 01:12:33.970
Yeah. okay. Bye.

1127
01:12:44.384 --> 01:12:47.384
If. you know. you hear a hint
of pain in my voice

1128
01:12:49.622 --> 01:12:52.424
when I say that I've
lost my best friend

1129
01:12:52.425 --> 01:12:55.425
to a gang of
roller skating she-males

1130
01:12:56.496 --> 01:12:59.496
and that the only highlight of my
night was serving corn to an old man

1131
01:12:59.832 --> 01:13:02.832
who can't even chew it.
then I'd say you're wrong.

1132
01:13:06.572 --> 01:13:09.572
I'm happy.

1133
01:13:24.290 --> 01:13:27.290
Okay. That was odd.

1134
01:13:32.098 --> 01:13:35.098
Oddly glorious.

1135
01:13:35.301 --> 01:13:38.301
Ruthless. what's up?

1136
01:13:38.805 --> 01:13:41.805
I just had something
I wanted to tell you all.

1137
01:13:42.475 --> 01:13:44.443
Seventeen?

1138
01:13:44.444 --> 01:13:45.711
What if you'd
gotten hurt?

1139
01:13:45.712 --> 01:13:47.879
Her parents could sue
the league. you guys.

1140
01:13:47.880 --> 01:13:48.981
I know.

1141
01:13:48.982 --> 01:13:50.983
We're in enough trouble
with the fire marshal as it is.

1142
01:13:50.984 --> 01:13:52.718
Exactly. You know what?
She can still play

1143
01:13:52.719 --> 01:13:55.719
as long as she gets permission
from one of her parents.

1144
01:13:58.324 --> 01:13:59.825
I can't.

1145
01:13:59.826 --> 01:14:02.826
I'm not even living
at home right now.

1146
01:14:03.062 --> 01:14:06.062
Well. even though you can't skate
with us. and you're a big liar.

1147
01:14:07.633 --> 01:14:09.868
you're still
a Hurl Scout.

1148
01:14:09.869 --> 01:14:12.170
Yeah. you could
be our mascot.

1149
01:14:13.506 --> 01:14:16.506
- Okay. go.
- Okay. okay. okay.

1150
01:14:17.643 --> 01:14:20.643
You can't understand until you
have one. Everything changes.

1151
01:14:23.583 --> 01:14:26.583
Yeah. that's what
my mom always says.

1152
01:14:26.586 --> 01:14:28.553
but you're not
really like her. though.

1153
01:14:28.554 --> 01:14:29.921
Oh. I'm the cool aunt?

1154
01:14:29.922 --> 01:14:31.156
Yeah.

1155
01:14:34.594 --> 01:14:37.594
Why don't I just cut school and
hang out with you guys today?

1156
01:14:39.732 --> 01:14:41.500
Bliss. I know what it's like
to wanna do your own thing.

1157
01:14:41.501 --> 01:14:42.701
believe me. I do.

1158
01:14:42.702 --> 01:14:45.404
But maybe there's
a way you can do it

1159
01:14:45.405 --> 01:14:48.405
without making your parents
feel like crap?

1160
01:14:49.275 --> 01:14:51.276
What?
I've just been thinking.

1161
01:14:51.277 --> 01:14:54.277
I think maybe you're being
a little selfish with your mom.

1162
01:14:59.786 --> 01:15:02.786
Okay. no.

1163
01:15:02.789 --> 01:15:05.624
She's the one who has been
shoving her agenda

1164
01:15:05.625 --> 01:15:08.625
down my throat
since day one.

1165
01:15:09.028 --> 01:15:12.028
First of all. you're lucky to have
a mom that even cares.

1166
01:15:12.598 --> 01:15:14.466
And just because
she's wrong about derby.

1167
01:15:14.467 --> 01:15:17.467
doesn't mean she's wrong
about every single thing.

1168
01:15:17.870 --> 01:15:20.870
And if Riley ever lies to me the way
you lied to your parents.

1169
01:15:21.140 --> 01:15:23.708
he wouldn't even be able to run
away 'cause I'd break his legs.

1170
01:15:24.977 --> 01:15:27.779
I'm just kidding. honey.
That was a joke.

1171
01:15:30.450 --> 01:15:31.983
I am here for you.

1172
01:15:31.984 --> 01:15:34.984
but just because you've found a new family
doesn't mean you throw the old one away.

1173
01:15:48.501 --> 01:15:51.501
Have a swell day at
school. sweetheart.

1174
01:15:53.673 --> 01:15:56.673
You didn't see that.
did you?

1175
01:16:22.101 --> 01:16:25.101
I put a bomb in your fire
You say oh-oh-oh-oh

1176
01:16:25.538 --> 01:16:28.538
I put a bomb in your fire
You say oh-oh-oh-oh

1177
01:16:29.208 --> 01:16:32.208
There is a way to predict
the outcome of people like you

1178
01:16:36.382 --> 01:16:39.382
You are a sheep in sheep's clothing
and you know. you know...

1179
01:17:14.086 --> 01:17:17.086
Please don't
judge me right now.

1180
01:17:23.329 --> 01:17:26.329
Whoever he is.
he doesn't deserve you.

1181
01:17:30.770 --> 01:17:33.770
Come here.

1182
01:17:36.776 --> 01:17:39.544
I feel sick.

1183
01:17:39.545 --> 01:17:42.545
I know you do.

1184
01:17:51.290 --> 01:17:53.725
I gave him everything.

1185
01:17:53.726 --> 01:17:56.726
No. don't say that.

1186
01:18:05.471 --> 01:18:08.471
No. it's true.

1187
01:18:09.642 --> 01:18:12.642
I did.

1188
01:18:40.172 --> 01:18:43.172
That's a lot to process.

1189
01:18:48.514 --> 01:18:51.514
She was wearing
my Stryper T-shirt.

1190
01:18:51.951 --> 01:18:54.286
I just don't understand
how he could do that.

1191
01:18:54.287 --> 01:18:57.287
Your T-shirt?

1192
01:18:57.590 --> 01:19:00.258
It's the only
cool thing you own.

1193
01:19:00.259 --> 01:19:01.960
That you'd know about.

1194
01:19:03.162 --> 01:19:06.162
Stryper.

1195
01:19:10.469 --> 01:19:13.469
Mom. this isn't...

1196
01:19:13.472 --> 01:19:16.472
This isn't working.

1197
01:19:17.810 --> 01:19:20.178
I know.

1198
01:19:20.179 --> 01:19:23.179
You just make me
feel so guilty.

1199
01:19:23.883 --> 01:19:26.883
That's not what I want.

1200
01:19:29.455 --> 01:19:31.890
I deserve it sometimes.

1201
01:19:31.891 --> 01:19:34.891
Well. I know I can go
overboard sometimes.

1202
01:19:39.965 --> 01:19:42.965
But when the person that
you love more than anything

1203
01:19:43.536 --> 01:19:46.536
tells you
that you suck. it...

1204
01:19:49.342 --> 01:19:52.342
If you want me to do the
Miss Blue Bonnet pageant. I will.

1205
01:19:53.079 --> 01:19:56.079
No. no. no. no.
We're way past that.

1206
01:19:56.215 --> 01:19:59.215
No. it's not a big deal.
I mean. we already got the dress.

1207
01:20:04.757 --> 01:20:07.757
Don't do it for me.

1208
01:20:08.227 --> 01:20:10.695
Fine. I'll do it
for myself.

1209
01:20:17.870 --> 01:20:20.705
Look who's back.

1210
01:20:20.706 --> 01:20:23.706
Hi.

1211
01:20:29.281 --> 01:20:32.281
Glad you're safe.

1212
01:20:33.386 --> 01:20:36.386
I shouldn't have said
those things to you.

1213
01:20:40.092 --> 01:20:43.092
Already forgotten. kiddo.

1214
01:20:52.071 --> 01:20:55.071
She's trying to
look pathetic on purpose.

1215
01:20:59.044 --> 01:21:02.044
How long you gonna
hold onto that grudge?

1216
01:21:12.158 --> 01:21:15.158
Thanks.

1217
01:21:16.629 --> 01:21:19.264
Pash. I'm sorry.
You see. I just...

1218
01:21:19.265 --> 01:21:20.832
Come on.

1219
01:21:20.833 --> 01:21:23.833
I'm sorry.

1220
01:21:25.171 --> 01:21:28.006
I'm really sorry.

1221
01:21:28.007 --> 01:21:31.007
I know.

1222
01:21:31.110 --> 01:21:33.611
Just keep...
Keep saying it.

1223
01:21:33.612 --> 01:21:34.746
Yeah.

1224
01:21:34.747 --> 01:21:36.181
Over and over
again. please.

1225
01:21:36.182 --> 01:21:39.182
Yeah. I will.
I'll keep it up.

1226
01:21:40.186 --> 01:21:41.419
So what happened?

1227
01:21:41.420 --> 01:21:44.420
God. I just feel
like such...

1228
01:21:45.357 --> 01:21:48.357
I'm stupid. I'm just...
I feel so stupid for falling for it.

1229
01:21:51.464 --> 01:21:54.464
Yeah. that's why I like a
good fondling. you know?

1230
01:21:54.533 --> 01:21:57.435
It's so much simpler.

1231
01:21:57.436 --> 01:22:00.436
Well. while you were
off gallivanting. I...

1232
01:22:03.709 --> 01:22:06.709
I got some news.

1233
01:22:07.146 --> 01:22:09.380
What... What... What's...

1234
01:22:09.381 --> 01:22:12.381
I got into some colleges.

1235
01:22:12.885 --> 01:22:14.052
Wow!

1236
01:22:14.053 --> 01:22:16.354
My parents want me
to go to Johns Hopkins.

1237
01:22:16.355 --> 01:22:19.355
but I think I'm
gonna go to Columbia.

1238
01:22:20.793 --> 01:22:23.793
I know. I'm gonna see what it's like
to live in New York for a little while.

1239
01:22:24.964 --> 01:22:27.964
That's amazing.

1240
01:22:33.339 --> 01:22:36.339
Do you still have
his stupid jacket?

1241
01:22:45.050 --> 01:22:47.318
Did he turn into
a handsome prince?

1242
01:22:47.319 --> 01:22:49.587
No. he stayed a Birdman.

1243
01:22:49.588 --> 01:22:52.588
But the worst part is.
he's actually a good kisser.

1244
01:22:54.426 --> 01:22:56.094
Really good.

1245
01:22:56.095 --> 01:22:58.263
Congratulations
are in order.

1246
01:22:58.264 --> 01:23:01.264
Uh. no. Let's not
encourage this.

1247
01:23:02.101 --> 01:23:04.335
I like Birdman.
He's nice.

1248
01:23:04.336 --> 01:23:07.336
Hey. Bliss. Somebody on the
phone for you. A Maggie Mayhem?

1249
01:23:09.241 --> 01:23:10.375
Well. look at you.

1250
01:23:10.376 --> 01:23:11.442
I got a makeover.

1251
01:23:11.443 --> 01:23:14.443
Yes. you did.

1252
01:23:18.117 --> 01:23:19.384
Hello.

1253
01:23:19.385 --> 01:23:20.785
Ruthless.
it's the championship.

1254
01:23:20.786 --> 01:23:23.254
Don't even tell me
you can't make it.

1255
01:23:23.255 --> 01:23:24.889
I can't.

1256
01:23:24.890 --> 01:23:27.890
Is it her mom? Let me talk
to her. I'll knock her out.

1257
01:23:29.261 --> 01:23:32.096
Just tell your mom
it's important.

1258
01:23:32.097 --> 01:23:34.933
The pageant is the same day
as the game. and I can't.

1259
01:23:34.934 --> 01:23:37.934
Well. you have to try harder and you
have to make it work. We need you.

1260
01:23:38.304 --> 01:23:39.804
Let me talk to her mom.
Bye.

1261
01:23:39.805 --> 01:23:42.805
I'll kick her in her...

1262
01:23:42.875 --> 01:23:45.875
You're selling out.

1263
01:24:00.726 --> 01:24:03.394
"Babe Ruthless. "

1264
01:24:03.395 --> 01:24:05.663
...a classic
move in derby.

1265
01:24:05.664 --> 01:24:08.664
Babe and Maggie go for the whip.
and it's effective.

1266
01:24:08.801 --> 01:24:11.801
Nothing gives you speed like a whip.
Look at Ruthless fly.

1267
01:24:22.948 --> 01:24:25.249
Excuse me. ladies.

1268
01:24:25.250 --> 01:24:28.250
I'm looking for Maggie.
Maggie Mayhem.

1269
01:24:33.525 --> 01:24:36.525
Good pageant. y'all.

1270
01:24:38.864 --> 01:24:41.864
Love the dress. Amber.

1271
01:24:44.937 --> 01:24:47.705
We'll have to break through.
I know.

1272
01:24:47.706 --> 01:24:50.706
What time is it?

1273
01:24:51.710 --> 01:24:54.545
Your gown is custom. huh?
Yeah.

1274
01:24:54.546 --> 01:24:56.881
It's beautiful.

1275
01:24:56.882 --> 01:24:59.882
Thanks.

1276
01:25:00.052 --> 01:25:03.052
Your dress is nice.
too. Amber.

1277
01:25:04.390 --> 01:25:07.390
Hey.
Hey.

1278
01:25:07.526 --> 01:25:10.526
We need to talk.

1279
01:25:14.633 --> 01:25:16.734
Ma'am. put down
the lip gloss.

1280
01:25:16.735 --> 01:25:18.236
Step away from the mirror.

1281
01:25:20.539 --> 01:25:23.539
What are you all doing
here? Are you... Hey. man.

1282
01:25:23.642 --> 01:25:25.243
You're just springing
this on me now?

1283
01:25:25.244 --> 01:25:26.844
I know the timing sucks.

1284
01:25:26.845 --> 01:25:29.080
but I've been thinking. You
know. I'm not so bothered

1285
01:25:29.081 --> 01:25:31.149
by her playing
this roller derby.

1286
01:25:31.150 --> 01:25:32.717
in fact. I think
it's kind of neat.

1287
01:25:32.718 --> 01:25:35.718
I went on the website. they got
Blisster's pictures all over.

1288
01:25:35.721 --> 01:25:37.588
And it looks like they're
having a ton of fun.

1289
01:25:37.589 --> 01:25:40.589
Earl. we just spent a lot of
money on a custom-made gown.

1290
01:25:42.027 --> 01:25:44.595
and you want her
to just up and quit?

1291
01:25:44.596 --> 01:25:47.098
Yeah. but her team is in
the league championships.

1292
01:25:47.099 --> 01:25:48.933
The game's tonight.

1293
01:25:48.934 --> 01:25:51.934
$800. Earl.

1294
01:25:55.374 --> 01:25:58.374
I can take
losing the money.

1295
01:25:58.444 --> 01:26:01.444
I cannot take losing the chance
for our kid to be happy.

1296
01:26:04.583 --> 01:26:06.851
I love her.
Yeah. she looks nice.

1297
01:26:06.852 --> 01:26:08.386
Really sweet.
- Bliss.

1298
01:26:08.387 --> 01:26:09.787
You guys gotta
hide. my mom's coming.

1299
01:26:09.788 --> 01:26:12.788
Bliss. Seriously.
You guys have to hide.

1300
01:26:13.358 --> 01:26:14.892
Hey.

1301
01:26:14.893 --> 01:26:16.394
Bliss.

1302
01:26:16.395 --> 01:26:19.395
Your daddy is about to come in here
and tell you that he thinks it's okay

1303
01:26:19.631 --> 01:26:22.631
for you to go off
and play roller derby.

1304
01:26:23.368 --> 01:26:25.203
I don't agree.
Mom.

1305
01:26:25.204 --> 01:26:28.204
When you told me that you weren't
doing the Miss Blue Bonnet for me.

1306
01:26:30.576 --> 01:26:33.576
did you mean it?

1307
01:26:42.154 --> 01:26:45.154
Well. good luck.

1308
01:27:03.776 --> 01:27:06.776
Come on. ladies.
What are we waiting for?

1309
01:27:07.913 --> 01:27:09.847
Ready to play.

1310
01:27:09.848 --> 01:27:12.848
Okay.

1311
01:27:15.187 --> 01:27:18.187
Wait. One more thing.

1312
01:27:21.193 --> 01:27:24.193
Yeah. Come on. let's go.
- Good luck. Amber.

1313
01:27:24.363 --> 01:27:27.363
Step it up.

1314
01:27:31.770 --> 01:27:34.105
That's when...

1315
01:27:34.106 --> 01:27:37.106
Hi.

1316
01:27:38.644 --> 01:27:40.878
I got it.

1317
01:27:40.879 --> 01:27:43.648
We just got back into town.
I came straight over.

1318
01:27:43.649 --> 01:27:46.649
I probably still smell
like the van. But...

1319
01:27:48.287 --> 01:27:51.287
I went on your website and saw
some girl wearing my Stryper T-shirt.

1320
01:27:51.890 --> 01:27:54.125
Oh. that girl...

1321
01:27:54.126 --> 01:27:56.527
She just climbed
into our van.

1322
01:27:56.528 --> 01:27:59.528
threw on your shirt.
She was an idiot.

1323
01:28:00.799 --> 01:28:03.568
You know. I don't
wanna be this girl.

1324
01:28:03.569 --> 01:28:05.636
What girl?

1325
01:28:05.637 --> 01:28:08.637
I don't wanna be the girl
that has to stand here

1326
01:28:10.475 --> 01:28:13.475
and hear about what didn't
happen between you and some idiot.

1327
01:28:14.680 --> 01:28:17.680
You don't. And this is bullshit. anyway.
I didn't cheat on you.

1328
01:28:20.652 --> 01:28:23.652
But you never
called. okay?

1329
01:28:24.189 --> 01:28:25.590
Okay.

1330
01:28:25.591 --> 01:28:28.591
I know I should've called. but there
was no privacy in the van.

1331
01:28:28.994 --> 01:28:31.994
And then I got
your message and...

1332
01:28:38.770 --> 01:28:41.770
I would've called.

1333
01:28:42.841 --> 01:28:45.841
My mom wants
her shirt back.

1334
01:28:52.451 --> 01:28:55.353
That's right. I'm back.

1335
01:28:55.354 --> 01:28:57.688
Thanks a lot for outing me.
That was a class move.

1336
01:28:57.689 --> 01:29:00.689
I didn't out you.
I never said a word.

1337
01:29:01.226 --> 01:29:02.960
I was just
messing with you.

1338
01:29:02.961 --> 01:29:04.962
I don't wanna beat
your ass with rumors.

1339
01:29:04.963 --> 01:29:07.963
I wanna beat your ass on
the track with my skates.

1340
01:29:09.067 --> 01:29:11.769
It is
happening tonight. folks.

1341
01:29:11.770 --> 01:29:13.971
There they are.
the coaches shaking hands.

1342
01:29:13.972 --> 01:29:15.706
being nice and diplomatic

1343
01:29:15.707 --> 01:29:18.707
right before the craziest match that
we will ever see here.

1344
01:29:20.279 --> 01:29:22.980
Oh. I love it. Austin.

1345
01:29:22.981 --> 01:29:24.282
That's right.
ladies and gentlemen.

1346
01:29:24.283 --> 01:29:27.051
we're talking about the
one and only Iron Maven

1347
01:29:27.052 --> 01:29:30.052
versus the upstart from the heart
of Texas. Babe Ruthless.

1348
01:29:32.491 --> 01:29:33.758
Yes.

1349
01:29:36.828 --> 01:29:39.163
Our jammers.
Ruthless versus Maven

1350
01:29:39.164 --> 01:29:42.164
head-to-head.
the teams. two top stars.

1351
01:29:43.001 --> 01:29:44.335
As they approach
the pack.

1352
01:29:44.336 --> 01:29:47.138
Ruthless seems to be having
an easier time finding an opening.

1353
01:29:47.139 --> 01:29:50.139
slithering through like a
proverbial snake in the grass.

1354
01:29:51.576 --> 01:29:54.512
There's Babe Ruthless.
Iron Maven. neck and neck.

1355
01:29:54.513 --> 01:29:57.513
They've been after each other
the whole time. Oh!

1356
01:29:58.183 --> 01:29:59.951
That's a hip check
right there.

1357
01:29:59.952 --> 01:30:01.953
You don't see Maven
taken down like that too often.

1358
01:30:01.954 --> 01:30:04.355
Did you see that?
Call it.

1359
01:30:04.356 --> 01:30:06.090
That was illegal. What are
you talking about?

1360
01:30:06.091 --> 01:30:07.191
It's a clean hit.

1361
01:30:07.192 --> 01:30:09.360
That was illegal.
Just call that shit.

1362
01:30:09.361 --> 01:30:12.196
Calm her down.

1363
01:30:12.197 --> 01:30:14.632
I'll show you ruthless.
Ruthless.

1364
01:30:17.102 --> 01:30:18.703
It's the
second quarter. folks.

1365
01:30:18.704 --> 01:30:21.704
We got Babe Ruthless jamming against
the Rollers. Jackie Daniels.

1366
01:30:25.143 --> 01:30:27.345
Finally. I made it
to the promised lands.

1367
01:30:27.346 --> 01:30:30.346
Okay. don't embarrass me
now that you're here. all right?

1368
01:30:30.549 --> 01:30:33.549
Never.

1369
01:30:34.219 --> 01:30:37.219
Go. Bliss. Go!

1370
01:30:37.322 --> 01:30:39.190
Go. Babe Ruthless!

1371
01:30:39.191 --> 01:30:41.225
Go!

1372
01:30:41.226 --> 01:30:42.626
Babe Ruthless
coming in to the pack.

1373
01:30:42.627 --> 01:30:44.161
but she's having
trouble getting out.

1374
01:30:44.162 --> 01:30:47.162
That tiny pipsqueak finds a hole.
but not as fast as Jackie Daniels

1375
01:30:47.966 --> 01:30:50.501
breaks out of the pack.
becomes the lead jammer.

1376
01:30:50.502 --> 01:30:53.502
Rollers just picked up four more points.
bringing the score 24-11.

1377
01:30:54.573 --> 01:30:56.407
Rollers in the lead.

1378
01:30:57.542 --> 01:30:59.744
Slaya takes down Smashley.

1379
01:30:59.745 --> 01:31:01.645
Oh. but the Mansons
grab those wings

1380
01:31:01.646 --> 01:31:04.646
and Smashley flies after Slaya
like a bat out of hell.

1381
01:31:08.020 --> 01:31:10.421
You just
clothesline me. man.

1382
01:31:13.425 --> 01:31:16.425
Princess Slaya.
feeling the force now.

1383
01:31:18.563 --> 01:31:21.563
That's gonna hurt tomorrow
in a galaxy far. far away.

1384
01:31:22.701 --> 01:31:24.702
Listen. You play smart.
stay aggressive.

1385
01:31:24.703 --> 01:31:26.937
Don't leave any holes for them to
slip through. all right?

1386
01:31:26.938 --> 01:31:29.607
Bliss. this may be time
for Play Number 4.

1387
01:31:29.608 --> 01:31:32.608
LBJ. Knock them out.

1388
01:31:34.613 --> 01:31:37.048
Coach Razor throws Ruthless in
the jammer's seat

1389
01:31:37.049 --> 01:31:38.749
as she makes her way
through the pack.

1390
01:31:38.750 --> 01:31:41.750
Look. she gets a hand from
Bloody Holly and slingshots out front.

1391
01:31:41.953 --> 01:31:43.120
This could be big.

1392
01:31:43.121 --> 01:31:46.121
And one of the Manson sisters sends
Maven hard into the rail.

1393
01:31:47.626 --> 01:31:50.626
Maven can yell all she wants.
but she can't hear you.

1394
01:31:52.564 --> 01:31:55.564
No. seriously. she can't hear you.
She's deaf. So...

1395
01:31:58.136 --> 01:32:01.136
I'll tell you what. The Holy Rollers have
got to lay some hits on Ruthless

1396
01:32:01.740 --> 01:32:03.707
if they're gonna have
any hopes of stopping her.

1397
01:32:03.708 --> 01:32:06.708
otherwise she's
just too quick.

1398
01:32:08.146 --> 01:32:11.146
All the Scouts dive-bombing
the Rollers. clearing the path.

1399
01:32:11.650 --> 01:32:14.650
Not one schoolgirl
left standing.

1400
01:32:15.654 --> 01:32:18.222
But we are tied as we
go into the half-time.

1401
01:32:18.223 --> 01:32:21.223
Ladies and gentlemen.
that was a game-changing down.

1402
01:32:33.405 --> 01:32:35.506
Okay. Razor.
what's next? Tell us what to do.

1403
01:32:35.507 --> 01:32:38.507
We're gonna run Play Number 7.
Rose of San Antone.

1404
01:32:38.844 --> 01:32:40.478
Hey. Smashley.
if the play was called Bong Water.

1405
01:32:40.479 --> 01:32:42.913
would you be paying
attention right now?

1406
01:32:42.914 --> 01:32:45.282
You know what. I'm taking you
out and putting Ruthless in.

1407
01:32:45.283 --> 01:32:48.283
No. My head
is in the game.

1408
01:32:49.588 --> 01:32:52.588
Then get out there
and prove me wrong.

1409
01:33:00.699 --> 01:33:03.033
Slaya hip-checks
Smashley into the rail.

1410
01:33:03.034 --> 01:33:05.803
She's up and over
and she's crowd surfing.

1411
01:33:05.804 --> 01:33:08.205
And Smashley Simpson
is back on the track.

1412
01:33:08.206 --> 01:33:10.474
Slaya and Smashley have been
at this all season. folks.

1413
01:33:10.475 --> 01:33:13.475
And it looks like Smashley
is speeding towards revenge.

1414
01:33:14.679 --> 01:33:15.779
I hope the medic is ready

1415
01:33:15.780 --> 01:33:18.780
'cause it looks like Slaya's about to
get a rainbow special.

1416
01:33:19.284 --> 01:33:22.219
This game's about
to get ugly. folks.

1417
01:33:22.220 --> 01:33:23.888
Wait. I don't
believe this.

1418
01:33:23.889 --> 01:33:26.889
Smashley goes for the points
instead of the beatdown...

1419
01:33:27.225 --> 01:33:30.225
That is for you. Razor!
... and picks up four for her team.

1420
01:33:32.230 --> 01:33:35.230
Okay. we're running Play Number 10.
Pièce de résistance.

1421
01:33:35.667 --> 01:33:37.401
Get back out there
and win it.

1422
01:33:37.402 --> 01:33:40.402
All right.

1423
01:33:40.805 --> 01:33:43.805
Let's go. you know what
to do. Get you some.

1424
01:33:44.209 --> 01:33:45.743
The game's still
too close to call.

1425
01:33:45.744 --> 01:33:47.878
but the Scouts may have some tricks
up their sleeves.

1426
01:33:47.879 --> 01:33:50.247
Looks like they're forming a wall.
Kaboom!

1427
01:33:50.248 --> 01:33:53.248
The entire Rollers team is
down as Ruthless flies through.

1428
01:33:55.520 --> 01:33:57.922
Wait. out of nowhere.
Jackie Daniels...

1429
01:34:26.284 --> 01:34:29.284
She's okay. She's okay.
That little munchkin's a trouper.

1430
01:34:29.788 --> 01:34:31.088
Give it up. folks.

1431
01:34:40.398 --> 01:34:43.300
Let's remember that derby
is a brutal sport.

1432
01:34:43.301 --> 01:34:46.136
We've seen our fair share
of sprained ankles and broken bones.

1433
01:34:46.137 --> 01:34:48.205
fishnet burns
and black eyes.

1434
01:34:50.275 --> 01:34:52.476
It's the final jam.

1435
01:34:52.477 --> 01:34:54.979
Two points
deciding Austin's fate.

1436
01:34:54.980 --> 01:34:57.980
Let me hear you. folks.
Give it up for these girls.

1437
01:34:59.584 --> 01:35:02.486
It's Iron Maven
versus Babe Ruthless.

1438
01:35:02.487 --> 01:35:04.788
Would you have it
any other way?

1439
01:35:04.789 --> 01:35:07.789
The Mansons play Maven
in the middle of a patented cage move.

1440
01:35:09.628 --> 01:35:11.996
They're calling for the whip. and
they just might get what they want.

1441
01:35:11.997 --> 01:35:14.997
They got it.

1442
01:35:21.573 --> 01:35:24.573
Go. Maven.

1443
01:35:24.976 --> 01:35:26.143
Ruthless gets out first.

1444
01:35:26.144 --> 01:35:28.145
And now as she gets a hand
from Bloody Holly...

1445
01:35:28.146 --> 01:35:31.146
No. Maven sneaks out from the
inside and is heading for the lead.

1446
01:35:31.349 --> 01:35:34.349
But wait. the Manson sisters
line up. A double leg whip.

1447
01:35:51.169 --> 01:35:54.169
Ruthless is surging ahead.
She can taste the victory.

1448
01:35:54.939 --> 01:35:57.041
But no.

1449
01:35:57.042 --> 01:35:58.509
That's it.

1450
01:35:58.510 --> 01:36:01.510
Iron Maven brings
down the anvil.

1451
01:36:01.546 --> 01:36:04.481
The Holy Rollers
remain undefeated

1452
01:36:04.482 --> 01:36:07.351
and are league champions
yet again.

1453
01:36:09.854 --> 01:36:12.854
The Holy Rollers
are champs.

1454
01:36:14.059 --> 01:36:17.059
Undefeated three years
in a row. Unbelievable.

1455
01:36:18.496 --> 01:36:20.798
What a game.

1456
01:36:20.799 --> 01:36:23.734
You gotta take your hat off to
both teams. ladies and gentlemen.

1457
01:36:23.735 --> 01:36:26.735
As for the Hurl Scouts.
there's always next year.

1458
01:36:28.640 --> 01:36:31.640
But this year it's a
three-peat for the Holy Rollers.

1459
01:36:32.344 --> 01:36:34.645
once again.
three-time champions.

1460
01:36:34.646 --> 01:36:35.879
I'm sorry. Razor.

1461
01:36:35.880 --> 01:36:38.880
Sorry. my ass.
You were great.

1462
01:36:38.917 --> 01:36:40.684
Still. who do they
love the most?

1463
01:36:40.685 --> 01:36:42.586
Did you see
that leg whip?

1464
01:36:42.587 --> 01:36:45.389
How about that jump
by Ruthless?

1465
01:36:45.390 --> 01:36:48.390
Smashley's dive
was hall of fame.

1466
01:36:49.260 --> 01:36:52.260
Yeah! Holy Rollers!

1467
01:36:54.766 --> 01:36:55.933
